The paper proposes a novel routing strategy that integrates vehicle powertrain dynamics into route optimization. This involves decision-making processes that consider factors such as vehicle powertrain type, battery state of charge, and component efficiencies under traffic conditions. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) and Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories, as it deals with the optimization of vehicle systems. Additionally, the paper involves the use of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques to optimize the routing strategy. Finally, the paper also involves information theory (cs.IT) as it considers the impact of sensory information from the vehicle powertrain on route optimization.
